{"_id": "bewitchingstudies", "name": "Bewitching Studies", "type": "feat", "img": "icons/svg/book.svg", "system": {"description": {"value": "Bewitching Studies\nAt 1st level, you gain Target Practice and one of the following features."}}, "effects": [], "flags": {}}
{"_id": "targetpractice", "name": "Target Practice", "type": "feat", "img": "icons/svg/book.svg", "system": {"description": {"value": "Target Practice: You've honed your aim to be able to strike very specifically with your dueling Charms. When casting a Charm, you can target specific items or body parts, as well as restrict the effects of the charm to only that specific item or body part."}}, "effects": [], "flags": {}}
{"_id": "lightningfastwand", "name": "Lightning Fast Wand", "type": "feat", "img": "icons/svg/book.svg", "system": {"description": {"value": "Lightning Fast Wand: You've honed your senses to be able to strike very specifically with your dueling Charms. Whenever you add your spellcasting ability modifier to a spell attack roll, add half your Dexterity modifier (rounded up) as a bonus as well. Additionally, you have advantage on initiative rolls."}}, "effects": [], "flags": {}}
{"_id": "protectiveenchantments", "name": "Protective Enchantments", "type": "feat", "img": "icons/svg/book.svg", "system": {"description": {"value": "Protective Enchantments: You gain access to the Protego spell. Additionally, when you cast a Protego, you may choose to affect a friendly creature within 30 feet. When you or a friendly creature is affected by one of your protego spells, they may roll 1d4 and add that number to the AC bonus of the spell.\n\nAt Higher Levels. At 5th level you gain access to the protego maxima spell, and when you cast a protego or protego maxima as a reaction, you may cast either spell a second time as a free reaction per round."}}, "effects": [], "flags": {}}
{"_id": "masteredcharms", "name": "Mastered Charms", "type": "feat", "img": "icons/svg/book.svg", "system": {"description": {"value": "Mastered Charms\nAt 4th level, you can optionally take this feature in place of an Ability score Improvement or Feat.\n\nMastered Charms: Increase your Dexterity score by 1, to a maximum of 20. Additionally, you have honed your skills with charms spells to be able to cast quickly and accurately. Choose five of your known cantrips as your Mastered Charms. You can cast each of them once with the use of a bonus action without expending sorcery points. When you do so, you can’t do so again until you finish a short or long rest."}}, "effects": [], "flags": {}}
{"_id": "advancedcharmswork", "name": "Advanced Charmswork", "type": "feat", "img": "icons/svg/book.svg", "system": {"description": {"value": "Advanced Charmswork\nAt 6th level, you gain one of the following features."}}, "effects": [], "flags": {}}
{"_id": "rapidcasting", "name": "Rapid Casting", "type": "feat", "img": "icons/svg/book.svg", "system": {"description": {"value": "Rapid Casting: Whenever you cast a Charms spell as an action, you may cast another locked in Charms spell of 3rd level or lower as a part of that action.\n\nThe number of Charms spells you can cast per action increases to three when you reach 10th level and to four when you reach 18th level."}}, "effects": [], "flags": {}}
{"_id": "professionalcharmer", "name": "Professional Charmer", "type": "feat", "img": "icons/svg/book.svg", "system": {"description": {"value": "Professional Charmer: You have learned how to improve and even perfect your charms spells. You gain access to the Professional Charms spell enhancements listed at the end of this subclass."}}, "effects": [], "flags": {}}
{"_id": "doublecast", "name": "Double Cast", "type": "feat", "img": "icons/svg/book.svg", "system": {"description": {"value": "Double Cast\n\nAt 9th level you’ve developed a heightened awareness of magical balance. When you cast a spell of 1st level or higher that does not deal damage, you can choose one additional target for the same spell within range, without expending an additional spell slot.\n\nYou can use this feature once per long rest."}, "uses": {"value": 1, "max": 1, "per": "lr"}}, "effects": [], "flags": {}}
{"_id": "powerfulmagic", "name": "Powerful Magic", "type": "feat", "img": "icons/svg/book.svg", "system": {"description": {"value": "Powerful Magic\nAt 10th level, you gain one of the following features."}}, "effects": [], "flags": {}}
{"_id": "durablespellwork", "name": "Durable Spellwork", "type": "feat", "img": "icons/svg/book.svg", "system": {"description": {"value": "Durable Spellwork: The magic you channel helps ward off harm. While you maintain concentration on a spell, you have a +2 bonus to AC and all saving throws. "}}, "effects": [], "flags": {}}
{"_id": "issuedcommand", "name": "Issued Command", "type": "feat", "img": "icons/svg/book.svg", "system": {"description": {"value": "Issued Command: You have shown your allies that trusting in your knowledge of charmswork will help in a pinch. Once per round, you may interact with an ally and command them to cast one of your locked in charms spells. Your ally does not have to have the spell attempted and does not gain a successful casting attempt when following this command. \n\nYou may issue a command a number of times equal to half your proficiency bonus per long rest."}}, "effects": [], "flags": {}}
{"_id": "refinedtechniques", "name": "Refined Techniques", "type": "feat", "img": "icons/svg/book.svg", "system": {"description": {"value": "Refined Techniques\nAt 14th level, you gain one of the following features."}}, "effects": [], "flags": {}}
{"_id": "wandandshield", "name": "Wand and Shield", "type": "feat", "img": "icons/svg/book.svg", "system": {"description": {"value": "Wand and Shield: You've uncovered an ancient dueling style, allowing both offense and defense at the same time. When you cast protego or protego maxima, you can transition the spell's casting to your off-hand, freeing up your wand to cast other spells. The spell's dedication now expends a bonus action instead of an action, and you are able to cast and maintain another concentration or dedication spell with your wand. Any factor that affects maintaining concentration is applied individually to each effect (e.g. upon taking damage make a Constitution saving throw for each spell)."}}, "effects": [], "flags": {}}
{"_id": "soundofsilence", "name": "The Sound of Silence", "type": "feat", "img": "icons/svg/book.svg", "system": {"description": {"value": "The Sound of Silence: You are a master of being silent when it counts. If you don't already have it, Subtle Spell is added to your metamagic options and does not count towards your metamagic count. When you use the Subtle Spell metamagic to cast a spell of 1st level or lower silently, you can do so without expending a sorcery point. If you already have Subtle Spell as a metamagic, you may exchange it for a different metamagic of your choice."}}, "effects": [], "flags": {}}
{"_id": "pinnacleofcasting", "name": "Pinnacle of Casting", "type": "feat", "img": "icons/svg/book.svg", "system": {"description": {"value": "Pinnacle of Casting\nAt 18th level, you gain one of the following features."}}, "effects": [], "flags": {}}
{"_id": "calledshot", "name": "Called Shot", "type": "feat", "img": "icons/svg/book.svg", "system": {"description": {"value": "Called Shot: Your work to be able to strike enemies under pressure has hit its peak. If you miss with a spell attack roll, you can roll it again with advantage. You can use this feature twice per rest."}, "uses": {"value": 2, "max": 2, "per": "sr"}}, "effects": [], "flags": {}}
{"_id": "forceofwill", "name": "Force of Will", "type": "feat", "img": "icons/svg/book.svg", "system": {"description": {"value": "Force of Will: Whenever a creature makes a saving throw against one of your Charms spells, it must do so at disadvantage. Additionally, any charm spell you cast that affects an area (cube, line, sphere, or cone) has its area's size doubled."}}, "effects": [], "flags": {}}
{"_id": "spellprotego", "name": "Protego", "type": "spell", "img": "icons/svg/shield.svg", "system": {"level": 1, "school": "abj", "description": {"value": ""}}, "effects": [], "flags": {}}
